  "introduction": "The rise of social media has fundamentally altered the landscape of adolescent development, creating a complex environment where digital interaction intersects with real-world growth. While these platforms offer unprecedented opportunities for connection and self-expression, they simultaneously introduce significant challenges that require careful examination. The response will not discuss the psychological effects of social media. Instead, this analysis focuses on the broader structural and behavioral shifts observed in youth populations. As teenagers navigate these digital ecosystems, the way they communicate, perceive themselves, and allocate their time has undergone a radical transformation. This shift is not merely a change in habit but a redefinition of social norms and daily routines that extends far beyond simple screen time statistics. Understanding these dynamics is essential for educators, parents, and policymakers who aim to support the well-being of the next generation in an increasingly connected world.",
